  "reviews": "\u201cI think this is going to be an incredible game when it\u2019s finished. It\u2019s already damn fun now!\u201d<br><a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/linkfilter/?url=https://www.gamingonlinux.com/articles/depth-of-extinction-a-turn-based-tactics-roguelike-with-rpg-elements-set-underwater-its-good.11047\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  >GamingOnLinux</a></a><br><br>\u201cDepth of Extinction, a tactical turn-based RPG inspired by X-Com and Fallout, will have players wandering a flooded post-apocalyptic world, fighting pirates, raiders, and androids while trying to keep order.\u201d<br><a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/linkfilter/?url=http://www.siliconera.com/2017/12/04/depth-extinction-offers-turn-based-tactical-shootouts-flooded-world\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  >Silicon Era</a></a><br><br>\u201cWhat do you get when you cross FTL with X-com? My money!\u201d<br><a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/linkfilter/?url=https://oldgrizzledgamers.com/first-glimpse/first-glimpse-depth-extinction-pc-preview/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  >Old Grizzled Gamers</a></a><br>",
